THE ROLE
Expand all
Position Summary
New York University Abu Dhabi (NYUAD) seeks to appoint a Swim Coach for the Athletics department.
The Swim Coach will be required to demonstrate leadership in and out of the pool by developing and implementing a comprehensive swim program catering to all levels of students. The selected candidate will manage all the practice sessions, recruit students, organize events and look after all other aspects of coaching. S/he will monitor the academic progress of student athletes and promote the best interests of NYUAD by developing and maintaining effective relationships with faculty, staff and students.
Key Responsibilities
- Organize and administer NYUAD swim program
- Teach physical education swim classes and other community based classes
- Practice management and coaching
- Organize and host intercollegiate and interscholastic events
- Recruiting student-athletes
- Monitor academic progress of student
REQUIREMENTS
Education Requirements
- Bachelorâs degree in Physical Education, Sports Science, Kiinesiology, or a relevant discipline
- Current CPR/AED and First Aid certification
- Current lifeguard certification from American Red Cross or equivalent
- Water Safety Instructor (WSI) certification from American Red Cross or equivalent
Experience Requirements
- Minimum two years of experience in a similar role as a swim coach and instructor in a high school/collegiate athletic environment
- At least two years of swim instruction to all levels from beginner to advance
- Strong knowledge of standard operational procedures, safety rules and regulations in a pool environment
ABOUT THE COMPANY
NYU Abu Dhabi is a research university with a fully integrated liberal arts and science college. It draws students from around the world, and prepares them for the challenges and opportunities of our interconnected world.
